  <summary date="2021-01-14T14:52:42Z" status="Introduced in Senate">Younger Onset Alzheimer's Disease Act

This bill makes individuals with younger-onset Alzheimer's disease (i.e., individuals who experienced onset of the disease before age 60) eligible for certain federal grants and programs that support older adults. Under current law, these grants and programs serve only individuals 60 and older.</summary>
